Text.Value: I have to admit, I don't love sitting down for a chat with people who've relentlessly hunted me.
All right, we're listening.
I feel we're intruding. We should leave. Quickly.
I know our plight is grim, but if there is even a chance to save them, we must take it.
If we cannot have our children back, at least we will have justice.
If our children are truly gone, then we ask for blood. I know you can understand that, spawn.
*You recognise the funeral rites of the Gur people - a tribe of monster hunters. Their leader is burning the possessions of those who have fallen.*
You have lived a life of violence and sin. You have stolen lives, broken families, and caused immeasurable grief.  Doing this will not right those wrongs.
*You recognise the language of the Gur people, sprinkled with words from ancient Rashemi tongues, but you cannot follow what's being said.*
Frey vald isk durovna. Frey vald isk ablast.

EditorData.NodeContext: FREY vald isk dur-OF-nah. FREY vald isk ab-LAST

Text.Value: If you're trying to encourage me, you're failing abysmally.
Astarion's refusing to help you. I thought you should know.
Is it true you left your master? That you broke the spell that binds you to him?
And once inside, you could do what we could not. You could save the children you damned.
Calm yourself - you will not be harmed. Our leader has called off the hunt. She wishes to speak to you.
If you want to throw him on that pyre, I fully support that.
Oh - eh... hello again?
You do not decide where I should be. Not now, not ever.
If Astarion won't help you, then I will.
Please, go. Time is short, but we will see you again when it is done.
You don't know Cazador like I do - he's merciless.
And you have brought a sombre guest. I did not think you would willingly return, spawn.
But it will be a start. You may still be redeemed.
You pledged to help us. Have you so quickly gone back on your word?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Met Ulma without Astarion before. Now you meet her with Astarion as your companion.

Text.Value: We have tried to save our children once already, attacking Cazador Szarr's palace at first light. Even then, it was too well defended.
Gods damn it - fine! If nothing else, at least killing Cazador will feel good.
Free? Not while his master still lives. But he has, perhaps, earned a second chance.
We are not. But perhaps we can give you a chance to do deeds just as worthy of song.
When we sent Gandrel after you, we wanted to interrogate you. To discover how to save our children and then destroy you.
Well, I mean... kind of? It's a long story, honestly.

EditorData.stateContext: Ulma standing, talking to players in normal positioning

Text.Value: Frey vald isk durovna. Frey vald isk ablast.

EditorData.NodeContext: FREY vald isk dur-OF-nah. FREY vald isk ab-LAST

Text.Value: But you never saw him feed yourself? He could keep prisoners for days before killing them.
I hoped to find at least one monster that could be redeemed, but it seems not.
He's right. You're too late.
We can't help you. There's nothing more to discuss.
*She's speaking the language of the Gur people, one influenced by ancient Rashemi tongues. She's praying for the fallen of her tribe as their possessions are burned.*
Attack.
For those your friend stole from us, it is a matter of life and death.
Yes, Astarion's free now.
It was more dumb luck than any skill on his part.
Im orak ne tay. Krasin ne trah!

EditorData.NodeContext: IM or-AK nay tay. KRAS-in nay TRAH

Text.Value: I spent two hundred years bringing him victims. Each and every one was whisked away to be fed on that night.
We'll do it. We'll save them.
How can you be sure, Astarion?
*You do recognise the language, however. These people are Gur, a tribe of monster hunters.*
*You've clearly walked into some kind of ceremony, but it's nothing that you recognise.*
You want me to march into the lion's den and save your children, but I promise you, they're already dead.
Rech té i hathran roost.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Looking onto a pyre, where a variety of possessions are being burned - armour and broken weapons, as well as clothing,
EditorData.SFXTags: [DP] Ceremonial Pyre burning and crackling in the background

Text.Value: Then we have no use for you.
Even you, my erstwhile quarry.
Well, of course. To hells with you!
What do you want with Astarion?
So, the impossible spawn walks among us in the blazing sun. We have been looking for you.
I'm thinking of turning it into a ballad, if you're interested?
My friend from the hag swamp? You join us as we honour our fallen dead - you are a bright light on a dark day.
But if his own spawn approached? Someone he thought he could control? He would throw his doors open and welcome you in.
*You do recognise the language, however. These people are Gur, a tribe of monster hunters just like the one you met in the hag's swamp.*
*You recognise the funeral rites of the Gur people - the same monster hunters you met in the hag's swamp. Their leader is burning the possessions of those who have fallen.*
Im orak ne tay. Krasin ne trah!

EditorData.NodeContext: IM or-AK nay tay. KRAS-in nay TRAH

Text.Value: Welcome, friend. You've joined us as we honour our fallen dead - a sombre time.
I suppose... Yes. Yes, revenge I can do.

EditorData.NodeContext: Weighing his options, slightly reluctant to concede, but he will

Text.Value: One is just as important as the other, I find. And our luck has been poor.
So you leave us no choice. You are too dangerous to walk this world, spawn. If you cannot be redeemed, then you must be destroyed.
We want nothing to do with you.
You can take that olive branch and shove it.
When I was hunting you, I was to bring you back here. To interrogate you, discover how to save our children, and then destroy you.
But things have changed. You have changed.
Excuse me? Did you not hear anything I just said? They're gone.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Ulma pauses for a moment, staring at the fire in contemplation before she turns and walks over to the player.
EditorData.SFXTags: [DP] Ceremonial Pyre burning and crackling in the background

Text.Value: Well indeed. I was rather hoping I'd never see you people again, honestly.
Thank you, from me and all my people. If you can do this, we will be in your debt.
What business is it of yours?
What? You're handing me over to them?
What are you doing? You and the spawn should be at the palace, not here!
I am offering an olive branch. Do not knock it aside so quickly.

EditorData.stateContext: Ulma is standing in front of a burning pyre, arms raised, reciting funeral rites for fallen soldiers

Text.Value: You owe them revenge, Astarion. If nothing else, you owe them that.
You're monsters, all of you. Hunters, to me!
The last time your friend came to our camp, he stole our children. Our future.
No, of course not. We will go to Cazador's palace.
Thank you, now please go. We have lost enough time already.
I promise you, the thought did cross my mind.
